    "assignment": {
      "id": 1483176,
      "position": 2,
      "description": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401206/dp_app.css\"><div id=\"content\">This exercise is from Chapter 1 from&nbsp;<em>The Programmer's Brain&nbsp;</em>by Felienne Hermans. (<a title=\"Readings\" href=\"https://canvas.calpoly.edu/courses/172956/pages/readings\" data-course-type=\"wikiPages\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.calpoly.edu/api/v1/courses/172956/pages/readings\" data-api-returntype=\"Page\">See here if you're interested in reading more</a>.)\n<p>For two out of the three code snippets below, answer the questions posed in the table below. You can write your answers as plain text in the text entry box.</p>\n<p>Work with your tablemates. Only one group member needs to make a submission, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">including all group members' names</span>. (If you want to do an individual submission so that the Canvas notification goes away, feel free.)&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid black; padding: 12px 16px; text-align: left;\"></th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid black; padding: 12px 16px; text-align: center;\">Code snippet 1</th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid black; padding: 12px 16px; text-align: center;\">Code snippet 2</th>\n<th style=\"border-bottom: 2px solid black; padding: 12px 16px; text-align: center;\">Code snippet 3</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\">Are you retrieving knowledge from LTM?</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f9f9f9;\">\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\">If you are retrieving knowledge from LTM, what information?</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\">Are you storing information in your STM?</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f9f9f9;\">\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\">What information are you storing explicitly?</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\">What information are you ignoring because it seems irrelevant?</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f9f9f9;\">\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\">Is your working memory processing some parts of the code extensively?</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\">Which parts of the code place a heavy load on your working memory?</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"background-color: #f9f9f9;\">\n<td style=\"padding: 12px 16px;\">Do you understand why these parts of code make the working memory work?</td>\n<td style=\"padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 12px 16px;\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3 id=\"code-snippet-1-apl\">Code snippet 1 (APL)</h3>\n<p><img class=\"equation_image\" title=\"f \\leftarrow { \\omega \\leq 1 : \\omega \\diamond (\\nabla \\omega - 1) + \\nabla \\omega - 2}\" src=\"https://canvas.calpoly.edu/equation_images/f%2520%255Cleftarrow%2520%257B%2520%255Comega%2520%255Cleq%25201%2520%253A%2520%255Comega%2520%255Cdiamond%2520(%255Cnabla%2520%255Comega%2520-%25201)%2520%252B%2520%255Cnabla%2520%255Comega%2520-%25202%257D?scale=1\" alt=\"LaTeX: f \\leftarrow { \\omega \\leq 1 : \\omega \\diamond (\\nabla \\omega - 1) + \\nabla \\omega - 2}\" data-equation-content=\"f \\leftarrow { \\omega \\leq 1 : \\omega \\diamond (\\nabla \\omega - 1) + \\nabla \\omega - 2}\" data-ignore-a11y-check=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" x-canvaslms-safe-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>&amp;#x2190;<!-- \u2190 --></mo>\n  <mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;>\n    <mi>&amp;#x03C9;<!-- \u03c9 --></mi>\n    <mo>&amp;#x2264;<!-- \u2264 --></mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo>:</mo>\n    <mi>&amp;#x03C9;<!-- \u03c9 --></mi>\n    <mo>&amp;#x22C4;<!-- \u22c4 --></mo>\n    <mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>(</mo>\n    <mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x2207;<!-- \u2207 --></mi>\n    <mi>&amp;#x03C9;<!-- \u03c9 --></mi>\n    <mo>&amp;#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>)</mo>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x2207;<!-- \u2207 --></mi>\n    <mi>&amp;#x03C9;<!-- \u03c9 --></mi>\n    <mo>&amp;#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mrow>\n</math>\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"code-snippet-2-java\">Code snippet 2 (Java)</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"java language-java\">public class Luhn {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        System.out.println(luhnTest(\"49927398716\"));\n    }\n    public static boolean luhnTest(String number) {\n        int s1 = 0, s2 = 0;\n        String reverse = new StringBuffer(number).reverse().toString();\n        for(int i = 0; i &lt; reverse.length(); i++) {\n            int digit = Character.digit(reverse.charAt(i), 10);\n            if(i % 2  0) { //this is for odd digits\n                s1 += digit;\n            } else { //add 2 * digit for 0-4, add 2 * digit - 9 for 5-9\n                s2 += 2 * digit;\n                if(digit &gt;= 5) {\n                    s2 -= 9;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    return (s1 + s2) % 10  0;\n    }\n}</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"code-snippet-3-basic\">Code snippet 3 (BASIC)</h3>\n<pre><code>INPUT PROMPT \"String: \":TX$\nLET RES$=\" \"\nFOR I=LEN(TX$) TO 1 STEP-1\nLET RES$=RES$&amp;TX$(I)\nNEXT\nPRINT RES$</code></pre>\n</div><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401205/dp_app.js\"></script>",
