      "description": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401206/dp_app.css\"><p>Read&nbsp;<a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https://telearn.hal.science/hal-00190540/document\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The Buggy Path to the Development of Programming Expertise</em></a> by Roy Pea et al. and answer the following question prompts.</p>\n<p>Note that the paper is rather long \u2014 if you'd like, you can read up to and including the section on <strong>Metacognitive aspects of computer programming</strong> (page 14).</p><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads-pdx.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/account_152790000000000001/attachments/19401205/dp_app.js\"></script>",
